      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/182/1",
      "text": [
        ": مَنْ قَرَأَ سُورَهَ النَّحْلِ فِی کُلِّ شَهْرٍ کُفِیَ الْمَغْرَمَ فِی الدُّنْیَا وَ سَبْعِینَ نَوْعاً مِنْ أَنْوَاعِ الْبَلَایَا أَهْوَنُهُ الْجُنُونُ وَ الْجُذَامُ وَ الْبَرَصُ وَ کَانَ مَسْکَنُهُ فِی جَنَّهِ عَدْنٍ وَ هِیَ وَسَطُ الْجِنَانِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. From the previous chain from al-Hassan from ’Asim al-Khayyat from Muhammad b. Muslim from Abi Ja’far (a.s.) who said: “One who recites Surah Nahl every month would not see harm in the world and would be immune from seventy diseases the least of whom are insanity, leprosy and white spots. And his destination would be Jannat-e-Adn inside Paradise.”"
        ]
      }
    },
